      "content": "Eugenicists used the \"scientific\" reasoning that certain racial groups were inherently superior due to their physical characteristics, such as skin color, facial features, and body type. They claimed that these traits were evidence of superior intelligence, moral character, and adaptability, and that interbreeding between these groups would \"dilute\" their genetic superiority. They also believed that certain racial groups, particularly those with darker skin, were more prone to \"inferior\" traits such as laziness, promiscuity, and criminality. This ideology was perpetuated by pseudo-scientific theories like Social Darwinism and the concept of the \"Survival of the Fittest,\" which were used to justify forced sterilization, segregation, and other forms of oppression.",
